    "created_at": "2015-03-01T23:09:57Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-03-01T23:09:57Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "To give a more concrete example from my experience: an index corresponding to a variable like `longitude` might variously consist of integer (e.g., if it's in multiples of whole degrees) or as floating point numbers (e.g., if it's in multiples of half degrees). It's a bad user experience to need to cast their slice bounds to the type of index. Code like `s.loc[min_lon:max_lon]` should work regardless of dtypes.\n"
  },
